From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Entrpi <entrpi@proton.me>
Date: Sat, 6 Dec 2025 15:03:52 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] dma: arm-dma350: Fix audio pops by disabling register INTREN
 for cyclic DMA

For cyclic DMA transfers, disable the register-based interrupt enable
(CH_INTREN) and rely solely on the command link INTREN fields.

Previously, we enabled interrupts in both:
1. The CH_INTREN register (register-based)
2. Each command link entry's INTREN field

Having both interrupt sources enabled caused audio pops/clicks at period
boundaries during HDMI audio playback. The exact mechanism is unclear,
but it likely caused timing issues or race conditions when both sources
fired for the same completion event.

The vendor driver only uses command link INTREN for cyclic DMA and
explicitly disables register-based INTREN. This matches that behavior
and eliminates the audio artifacts.

Tested with HDMI audio playback on Radxa Orion O6 - pops are now gone.
---
 drivers/dma/arm-dma350.c | 10 +++++-----
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+), 5 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/dma/arm-dma350.c b/drivers/dma/arm-dma350.c
index 54d703ab16ce..1e7948c58c43 100644
--- a/drivers/dma/arm-dma350.c
+++ b/drivers/dma/arm-dma350.c
@@ -709,12 +709,12 @@ static void d350_start_cyclic(struct d350_chan *dch)
 	writel_relaxed(0, dch->base + CH_XSIZEHI);
 
 	/*
-	 * Enable interrupts BEFORE starting DMA.
-	 * The command link also has INTREN, but we set it early to avoid
-	 * any race condition where the first burst completes before
-	 * command link INTREN takes effect.
+	 * For cyclic DMA, disable register-based INTREN.
+	 * Let the command link entries control interrupts.
+	 * This matches vendor behavior and avoids potential issues
+	 * with both register and command link enabling interrupts.
 	 */
-	writel_relaxed(CH_INTREN_DONE | CH_INTREN_ERR, dch->base + CH_INTREN);
+	writel_relaxed(0, dch->base + CH_INTREN);
 
 	/* Enable channel first */
 	writel(CH_CMD_ENABLE, dch->base + CH_CMD);
